@4 File: Makefile (lines 15–22)

main.o: main.cpp riders.h → g++ -c main.cpp

riders.o: riders.cpp riders.h → g++ -c riders.cpp

tests.o: tests.cpp → g++ -c tests.cpp
The -c flag compiles each source file into an object file (.o) without linking.

Linking stage (lines 7–12):

main: main.o riders.o → links into executable.
Purpose: Faster rebuilds and modular compilation.
@5 Structure: DailyStats in main.cpp (lines 32–40) holds:

total_deliveries, total_money, missed_orders, plus per-vehicle stats.

Computation: In process_order() (main.cpp lines 137–185)

Updates totals when a rider is assigned: lines 168–177

Adds to missed_orders if no rider available: lines 182–184

Uses constants COST_STANDARD and COST_PRIORITY (lines 18–19).

Formula: total_orders = total_deliveries + missed_orders

Output: Written to .dat files by write_daily_summary() (lines 91–106).

@6 Test 1 – Rider Initialization

File: tests.cpp (lines 10–20)

Purpose: Verify get_name() and get_vehicle_type() return correct values.

Method: REQUIRE() assertions.

Test 2 – Moped Logic and Time Calculation

File: tests.cpp (lines 22–42)

Purpose: Test priority acceptance, long-distance orders, and calculate_time() precision.

Method: Multiple SECTIONs using REQUIRE and Approx.

Test 3 – Bicycle Rules and Mileage Limit

File: tests.cpp (lines 44–77)

Purpose: Ensure bicycles reject priority or >2-mile orders and enforce daily quota.

Method: Simulate accumulated distance, then assert next order validity.
